{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place tomatoes in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>4 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add reserved chopped tomatoes, lentils, water, 1 tsp salt and 1 pinch pepper. Place Varoma dish into position and weigh in aubergines. Sprinkle aubergines with ½ tsp salt and 1 pinch pepper.","Insert Varoma tray and weigh courgettes onto it. Sprinkle courgettes with ½ tsp salt and 1 pinch pepper then cover Varoma. Steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Towards end of steaming time, preheat oven to 160°C.","Remove Varoma. Spread a layer of aubergine and courgette slices over base of an oven-proof dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm), interspersed with each other. Pour over half the lentils. Arrange another layer of aubergine and courgette slices over lentils then cover with remaining lentils. Sprinkle with cheese.","Bake for 30-35 minutes (160°C) until golden. Remove from oven and allow to stand for a few minutes before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["600 g ripe tomatoes, quartered","3 garlic cloves","180 g onions, quartered","20 g extra virgin olive oil","250 g red split lentils, rinsed and drained","350 g water","2 tsp fine sea salt","3 pinches ground black pepper","300 g aubergines, sliced 7-8 mm (approx. 1 large)","300 g courgettes, sliced 7-8 mm (approx. 2 medium)","100 g vegan cheese, grated"]}],"id":"r115929","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-t27VlTpt4_8\/XZVP4rEu9xI\/AAAAAAAAc9w\/j_D1xK1d0J0v74SE2B8PRiU5XeUJwwh3wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Gw9Mc3Hi5ooy6jEE.png","title":"Aubergine, Courgette and Red Lentil Gratin","publishedAt":"2016-10-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.79 g","fat":"8.54 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"13.85 g","calories":"716 kJ \/ 171 kcal"},"usefulItems":"oven-proof dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Grate your own vegan cheese by placing pieces in mixing bowl and grating <strong>5 sec\/speed 4<\/strong>.","Tinned tomatoes can also be used instead of fresh ones. Omit step 1 and continue as per recipe.","Vegan cheese can be purchased at health food stores or from large supermarkets."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 10m","6 portions"]}